Package uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.owl.reason

Provides OWL/DL-reasoning based plugins for MEKON models (see uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.owl for general description).

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ORConfigVocab
    Vocabulary used in the ORClassifier and ORMatcher-definition sections of the MEKON configuration file.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    NetworkIRIs
    Utility for extracting IRIs for the concepts and properties associated with entities in the node/link network representation as provided by the uk.ac.manchester.cs.mekon.network package.
    ORClassifier
    Provides OWL-classification-based versions of the reasoning mechanisms defined by IReasoner, based on classifications involving either class-expressions or networks of individuals.
    ORClassifierLogger
    Logger for ORClassifier.
    ORConceptsMatcher
    Extension of ORMatcher that represents the instances as appropriately-defined OWL classes, which are added to an in-memory version of the ontology, and that represents queries as anonymous class-expressions.
    ORIndividualsMatcher
    Extension of ORMatcher that represents the instances as networks of individuals, which are added to an in-memory version of the ontology, and that represents queries as anonymous class-expressions.
    ORLogger
    Logger for ORClassifier and ORMatcher.
    ORMatcher
    Abstract base-class for OWL-based implementations of the matching mechanisms defined by IMatcher.
    ORMatcherLogger
    Logger for ORMatcher.
    ORMonitor
    Monitor for ORClassifier and ORMatcher operations.
    OROntologyBasedMatcher
    Base-class for ORMatcher-extensions that represent the instance as constructs in the ontology.
    ORSemantics
    Defines the open/closed-world semantics to be embodied by the OWL constructs that will be created and used by the reasoning mechanisms.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ORLoggingMode
    Specifies the type of reasoner-logging to be provided by instances of ORLogger.
    ORSemanticWorld
    Specifies the type of semantics to be embodied by the OWL constructs that will be constructed to represent property value-sets.
